title: For Sale:  Mosin Nagant 91/30 1934/52
postcontent:
Hex receiver Izhevsk manufactured Mosin dated 1934/52. Has Russian Ministry of Defense "MO" markings. Will include 150 rounds of surplus ammo.

MO is known to be the Russian abbreviation for "Ministerstvo Oborony", or Ministry of Defense. The Defense Ministry was established on March 15th, 1953. Based on information from sources in the former Soviet Union the MO marked firearms were used by the Defense Ministry Militarized Security force, or "Voenizirovannaya Ohrana MO", abbreviated VOHR MO. Those are not per se troops, but security guards employed by the MO. They wore military uniforms with special insignia of position (not rank insignia) and were separate from the army. These units were used to guard various MO facilities.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Want to trade 1951 Mauser k98k clone
postcontent:
This a k98k clone, the Yugo M48. Built in Serbia, not in a bombed out German factory. 

Made in the second year of production. Shaved bolt handle, and tapped receiver done at the factory. The way to tell the difference between original tapping and one done after is that original factory done did not mar the rifles model number. This is true m48, not a m48a, b, or Bo. This rifle has all milled parts. Only thing after market is low swing safety, timney adjustable trigger, and luepold scope mount. Original zrak mounts cost several hundred dollars, and are hard to find. The mount, trigger, and safety cost me over $200 on top of the rifle. You won't find a prettier example of a Mauser. 

Rifle and 2 stripper clips without ammo. $400
150rds of 8mm ammo(only appx 20 milsurp) $150

Sell all for $475, saving you $75

Email or text. 501-240-238four

title: For Sale:  Dan Wesson 7445 SuperMag
location: Will Drive to St. Cloud, Brainerd, Minnesota
postcontent:
Stainless Steel DAN WESSON 7445 chambered in the powerful .445 SuperMag cartridge designed by Elgin Gates. I am told that you can shoot .44 magnum out of these guns but I have never done it and this is the second one of these I have owned. Starline in Sedelia, Missouri makes brass for this amazing cartridge at a very reasonable price.

This one has the 8” barrel with the fluted shroud to make weight for the Production Revolver class in IHMSA competition.  There is at least one owner prior to me so I have no idea how many rounds have been fired through it but it does not appear to have been very many. I have fired about 50 rounds. Most of my hunting is with handguns but I seem to be gravitating to shorter barrels so this one is gathering dust in my safe.

According to my shipping scale the guns weighs, 4lbs and has some handling marks on it.  The trigger holds 3# but lets go before 3.5# on my RCBS trigger pull gage giving the clean break that the Wessons were know for. It has been drilled and tapped for a Burris Base and rings which are included in the purchase price along with a Hogue Monogrip, a set of Redding reloading dies (including a .44 caliber profile crimp die) and a barrel nut wrench that I made. I have some new Starline brass and a couple of Burris scopes that can be purchased separately. There is a 2X Burris in like new condition or a 1.75X4 Burris that has some paint missing from under the rings. Either scope can be added to the package for an additional $100.

There is no box or or original paper work. I have a copy of the large frame instruction manual that I downloaded from the internet that I can email or print out.

I am not a dealer. I do have the ability to accept a credit card through my business but there is a 3% up charge for that and must be completed prior to taking delivery of the firearm. I am willing to do some driving to complete the transaction with a serious buyer.

To complete the transaction you will need to provide cash, a valid Minnesota photo ID (drivers license), and either a Minnesota permit to purchase or a permit to carry. I will in return provide a bill of sale.

I prefer to be contacted by email. If you provide a phone number and best time to contact you I will call as soon as I can.

Thanks for your consideration!
